{{outdated|reason=the order of the list had minor changes, and the last two tied films have been replaced with O Palhaço. see https://abraccine.org/2016/09/04/abraccine-lanca-100-melhores-filmes-brasileiros-no-festival-de-gramado/|date=January 2018}}
In 2015, the [[Brazilian Film Critics Association]] (Abraccine) published a list with the 100 best [[Brazil]]ian films ever according to the votes of its members. This poll was the basis for a book named ''The 100 Greatest Brazilian Films'', published in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://abraccine.org/2015/11/27/abraccine-organiza-ranking-dos-100-melhores-filmes-brasileiros/|title=Abraccine organiza ranking dos 100 melhores filmes brasileiros|work=Abraccine - Associação Brasileira de Críticos de Cinema|date=27 November 2015|access-date=15 February 2016}}</ref> [[Cinema Novo]] [[film director|director]] [[Glauber Rocha]] is the director with the most films in the list: five; followed by [[Rogério Sganzerla]], [[Joaquim Pedro de Andrade]], [[Nelson Pereira dos Santos]], [[Hector Babenco]] and [[Carlos Reichenbach]], each with four films.
