{{lowercase title}} {{Infobox website | name = e-mahashabdkosh | logo = | logocaption = | screenshot = | collapsible = | collapsetext = | caption = | url = {{URL|http://e-mahashabdkosh.cdac.in}} | slogan = | commercial = | type = dictionary | registration = | language = English–Hindi | num_users = | content_license = | programming language = | owner = C-DAC | author = | editor = Ministry of Home Affairs, India | launch_date = <!-- {{Start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|df=yes/no}} --> | revenue = | alexa = | ip = | current_status = | footnotes = }} '''e-mahashabdkosh''' ({{lang-hi|ई-महाशब्दकोश}}) is an online dictionary website which is hosted and mentioned by Department of Official Language, India. This website is intended for general public use.
==About the site== E-Mahashabdakosh is an online bilingual-bidirectional Hindi–English pronunciation dictionary. In this dictionary basic meaning, synonyms, word usage and usage of words in special domain are included. This dictionary has the facility of search of Hindi and English words. The purpose of this dictionary is to provide a complete, correct, compact meaning and definition of a word.<ref name="rajbhasha">{{cite web|title=Annual report 2011-12|url=http://www.rajbhasha.nic.in/annualreporteng.pdf|publisher=Department of official language, Government of India|accessdate=1 September 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=हिंदी डिक्शनरी वेबसाइट्स, बस एक क्लिक दूर |trans-title=Hindi dictionary websites, just one click away|url=http://navbharattimes.indiatimes.com/techarticleshow/14201170.cms |publisher=[[Navbharat Times]]|accessdate=1 September 2013|date=17 June 2012|language=Hindi}}</ref>
==Development== During the year 2011–12, the work for the development of E-Mahashabdkosh for 12 work areas has been completed. During the year 2011–12, the work has been completed in additional four areas such as education, sports, culture and Railways.<ref name="rajbhasha" />
