[[File:MUSEO A.P.C..jpg|thumb|upright|Exterior view of the museum.]]

The '''Museo de Arte Antonio Paredes Candia''' is an [[art museum]] in [[El Alto, Bolivia|El Alto]], [[Bolivia]].

Inaugurated in 2002, as of 2011 the museum contains 503 works of art and 11,931 books.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eldiario.net/noticias/2009/2009_08/nt090828/5_06nal.php|title=Museo Antonio Paredes Candia es referente cultural|publisher=Eldiario|accessdate=26 June 2011|language=Spanish}}</ref> It includes works by Pérez Alcalá, Darío Antezana, Gil Imana, Alfredo Laplaca, [[Marina Núñez del Prado]], Víctor Zapana, [[Gonzalo Condarco]], and many more.

In 2013, organized by contemporary art collective [[Public Delivery]], Swiss-Bolivian artist Luciano Calderon had a solo show titled '''Ciudad Esperanza'''.<ref>http://publicdelivery.org/luciano-calderon-museo-de-arte-antonio-paredes-candia/</ref>

