{{Multiple issues|{{orphan|date=February 2009}}
{{notability|date=April 2017}}}}

The '''''Wapsipinicon Almanac''''' is an [[almanac]] published by Route 3 Press in [[Anamosa, Iowa]]. It is handmade on [[Letterpress printing|letterpress]] equipment by Timothy Fay and features stories, reviews, essays and poems. The first issue, published in 1988, sold out; the 2015 issue was the 22nd edition<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thegazette.com/subject/life/people-places/tim-fay-prints-the-wapsipinicon-almanac-on-antique-equipment-for-27-years-20151129|title=Tim Fay prints the Wapsipinicon Almanac on antique equipment for 27 years|last=Zabel|first=Liz|date=2015-11-29|work=The Gazette|access-date=2018-07-16}}</ref> and the latest edition went on sale around January 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://iowapublicradio.org/post/wapsipinicon-almanac-publishes-its-2018-edition#stream/0|title=Wapsipinicon Almanac Publishes its 2018 Edition|last=Nebbe|first=Charity|date=2018-01-12|work=Iowa Public Radio|access-date=2018-07-16|last2=Brod|first2=Robby|language=en}}</ref> 

